<TITLE> ADB South Asia chief to visit Bangladesh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, December 02 (bdnews24.com) -- Kunio Senga, Director General of the South Asia Department of the Asian Development Bank, is scheduled to arrive in Dhaka for one-day official visit on Wednesday. Senga will hold discussions with senior government officials, including the Adviser for Finance and Planning, Secretaries for the Economic Relations Division, Bridge Division, and Science and Information Communications Technology, ADB Dhaka said in a press release on Tuesday. The discussions will focus on issues related to ADB's proposed general capital increase as well as on implementation issues related to key operational sectors, including the multi-donor Second Primary Education Development Program, among other areas. ADB, based in Manila, is dedicated to reducing poverty in the Asia and Pacific region through pro-poor sustainable economic growth, social development, and good governance. Established in 1966, it is owned by 67 members  48 from the region. ADB's South Asia region comprises Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives, Nepal, and Sri Lanka.
